Marietta, GA 300635+ years experienceThis position is located in Iraq.
This position executes work on an international assignment in Iraq as the C-130 Customer Site Lead.
This program requires a highly motivated person to act as a liaison between the Contractor Maintenance Team (CMT) Team and the Iraqi Air Force (IqAF).
Role and responsibilities will include day-to-day operations for maintenance, supply and training of the IqAF in Iraq.
The on-site lead will interface with the USG Program Manager team to ensure joint management team efforts are fully coordinated and integrated to ensure Contractor tasks are properly managed and executed; will provide status and monitor any on-going schedule maintenance tasks; shall manage a sustainment logistics program for the C-130 consisting of logistics, sustainment, Package, Handling, Shipping, and Transportation (PHS&T), data support for materiel packing and shipping, systems familiarization, and data collection and reporting; coordinate with local sub-contractors; responsible for coordinating subordinate employee recruitment, selection and training, performance assessment, work assignments, salary, and recognition/disciplinary actions.
Acts as customer contact for program activities, participating in program review sessions with customer to discuss cost, schedule, and technical performance; identifies program problems and obtains solutions, such as allocation of resources or changes; maintain a good working relationship with IqAF customer personnel and be aware of and respect cultural differences at the host location.
As the site lead of this CMT team, manage all in-country requirements which will be instrumental to the IqAF’s ability to become a self sufficient Air Force.
Able to obtain or possess a current passport.
Must be able to obtain a US security clearance.Basic Qualifications:
5 years of aircraft maintenance management experience;
Experience in the areas of aircraft maintenance, operations and training;
Experience multi-tasking and prioritizing;
Experience interfacing with multiple levels of internal management and customers
Experience leading a teamDesired Skills:
Knowledgeable and conversant in military Maintenance, flight operations, safety, standardization, and supervision instructions and student management;
Demonstrated understanding of the importance of plans &
schedules;
Ability to utilize tools to manage all
projects/programs;
5 years experience on C-130J aircraft;
US DoD aviation maintenance, flight operations, and command experience;
A thorough working knowledge of TO military specifications;
Formal presentation skills, including the ability to interface at all levels and with multiple departments;
Ability to coordinate and communicate with US and Iraq Air Force leadership and personnel;
Must have strong professional interpersonal skills;
Experience in Foreign Military Sales (FMS) environment;
Experience working in a Security Level 5 country such as Iraq and/or Afghanistan; and
FAA A&P certificationBASIC QUALIFICATIONS:
